Job Description
Share
JOB PURPOSE
Prepare competency development frameworks and profiles for all positions related to specific assigned skill pool /job family, in applicable formats such as CAMS/CAMS, ZADCO CAMS, CAS, PDPs, CDPs and Professional Ladder.
Responsible
to provide Expert support and advice to MDCD & MDLE Teams
and troubleshoot issues in implementation of the competence development frameworks related to assigned discipline and supporting training matrix.
PRINCIPAL ACCOUNTABILITIES
* Prepare and enhance
competency development frameworks (CAMS,
ZADCO CAMS, CAS, and
PDPs) for assigned discipline(s), identifying the required critical competencies and
proficiency levels for each competency element in the framework.
* Ensure that the competency development framework is aligned with the target position Job requirement. Make necessary additions, amendments and enhancements to ensure its relevance to target positions.
* Prepare detailed behavior and performance criteria for each competency element,
as well as the required training courses
and on job real work assignments
to successfully achieve each competency element in the development framework.
* Develop and maintain a comprehensive database / inventory of real work tasks relevant for all positions in the assigned discipline and arrange to input the same in the
Oracle Learning Management System (OLM), for automatic generation of individualized personal development plans.
* Facilitate implementation of the
assigned discipline
Frameworks
by converting the programs in OLM format and automating the learning management for
all newly recruited employees, and providing support and
expertise guidance
to MD Teams for consistent and effective implementation of the assigned framework.
* Prepare, review and enhance Professional Ladders for assigned disciplines and Job families to enable continuous strengthening of competencies of the operational
employees.
* Prepare,
review and enhance the Career Development Programs (CDPs) and Competency Profiles (Standards) for all positions under assigned discipline.
* Conduct training and workshops for
development and familiarization and provide expertise guidance and support to MD Advisors/Instructors/Coaches and Assessors/Verifiers in implementing the assigned competency development framework and troubleshoot implementation issues.
* Keep up to date with latest innovations in competency development and management systems.
Participate in International Conferences and Seminars as Attendee and Speaker.
* Deliver training courses on assigned technical discipline as and when required.
* Provide input for reviewing the effectiveness of the
assigned DFW.
* Provide input in preparation of ADNOC People Dev. KPI & Organization Capability KPI reports.
Keyword: Competency
